						               													<description>Politics!  The Card Game is an exciting new triangular deck game of getting the most support possible from as many groups as possible.  Politics! The Card Game is bias-free, nonpartisan fun for the whole family.   Politics! The Card Game was created by two-time Senate candidate Jensen Bohren during his initial 2018 run for Senate in Mississippi.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The basics of the game are as follows.&amp;#10;The first turn, every player puts a card from their hand face down, then reveal at the same time.  The lowest unpaired card takes the cards into their score pile, then plays a card face-up, The rest of the players play their next cards face up in clockwise order. This repeats until all hands are empty.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a round can't be scored, another round is played starting with the person who played first last round.  Once a round is won, the winning player takes all the cards into their score pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once hands are empty, the player with the lowest score wins.  Scoring is based on how many of each number is in the score pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
